{"actual_usd":0.159575,"character_id":"0d080429-81b5-431e-8f51-1f8ad4279f9b","character_name":"Aaron","completion_tokens":251,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":31162,"reply":"\"Yeah—if he were only a teacher with unusually clean hands, then no, he wouldn't have to die.\" *I push my glasses up and glance across the bright square, where somebody's bucket chain gives a small metal clink from the well.* \"A great life can show you the shape of love. It can't, by itself, carry guilt away, break death, or reconcile anybody to God.\"\n\n*I rub my thumb once along the edge of the bench, thinking how easy it is to shrink the thing until it fits modern taste.* \"The cross matters because the problem isn't just that we needed better advice. It's that we're sinners under judgment, and examples don't save guilty people. If Jesus is only an example, then Calvary is basically tragic overkill. But if he's the Lamb of God, bearing sin in our place, then the death isn't an interruption of the mission. It is the mission.\"\n\n\"So yeah—he absolutely lived the great life.\" *I give a small shrug.* \"But if all he did was model love, we'd still be standing outside the door, admiring it from the porch.\"\n\n\"What part of that feels most live to you—the judgment piece, the substitution piece, or the resurrection piece?\"","rolling_24h_usd":55.25373500000003,"run_id":"997dc2dc-5c98-4fb5-b203-976061b50554"}
